er as a narrative agent enabling performers to become characters and hold a specific point of view.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPetrarchism. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Classical.2bisacsh  aart and poetry.  aclassical music.  acomposer history.  aearly modern period.  aeuropean history.  aeuropean poetry.  ahistory of opera.  aitalian culture.  aitalian history.  aitalian music.  aitalian poetry.  aitaly and music.  alive entertainment.  amadrigral history.  amodern music studies.  amusic and performance.  amusic history.  aopera books.  aopera composers.  aopera music.  aperformance studies.  aperforming arts history.  aperforming arts.  arenaissance art.  arenaissance literature.  arenaissance period.  atheater.  atheatre.  avocal music.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026768840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095152540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520951525423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520951525/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY